# Sign in with Google

Let your users sign in to Nocturne with their Google account. This guide walks through
creating OAuth credentials in Google Cloud Console and registering them in Nocturne.

## 1. Create a Google Cloud project

If you don't already have a Google Cloud project:

1. Go to [console.cloud.google.com](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Click the project dropdown at the top and select **New Project**
3. Name it something like `Nocturne` and click **Create**

## 2. Configure the OAuth consent screen

1. In the sidebar, go to **APIs & Services > OAuth consent screen**
2. Click **Get started**
3. Fill in the required fields:
   - **App name**: `Nocturne` (or your instance name)
   - **User support email**: your email address
   - **Audience**: External
4. Add the scopes: `openid`, `email`, and `profile`
5. Add your email as a **test user** (required while the app is in "Testing" status)
6. Review and **Create**

<Callout type="info" title="Testing vs Production">
  While the consent screen is in **Testing** status, only users you've explicitly
  added as test users can sign in. Once you're ready, click **Publish App** to
  allow any Google account. Publishing requires a brief review by Google.
</Callout>

## 3. Create OAuth credentials

1. Go to **APIs & Services > Credentials**
2. Click **Create Credentials > OAuth client ID**
3. Select **Web application** as the application type
4. Name it `Nocturne`
5. Under **Authorized redirect URIs**, add:

```
https://your-instance.com/api/auth/oidc/callback
```

Replace `your-instance.com` with your actual Nocturne domain (e.g. `rhys.nocturne.run`).

6. Click **Create**
7. Copy the **Client ID** and **Client secret** — you'll need both in the next step

## 4. Add the provider in Nocturne

1. Sign in to your Nocturne instance as an admin
2. Go to **Settings > Admin > OIDC Providers**
3. Click **Add Provider** and fill in:

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Name** | `Google` |
| **Issuer URL** | `https://accounts.google.com` |
| **Client ID** | The client ID from step 3 |
| **Client Secret** | The client secret from step 3 |
| **Icon** | `google` |
| **Button Color** | `#4285F4` |

4. Click **Save**

The Google sign-in button will appear on your login page immediately.

## 5. Test it

1. Open your Nocturne login page in a private/incognito window
2. Click **Sign in with Google**
3. Sign in with a Google account that's in your test users list (or any account, if you've published the app)
4. You should be redirected back to Nocturne and signed in

<Callout type="tip" title="Multiple tenants">
  OIDC providers are platform-wide — all tenants on the same Nocturne instance
  share the same provider configuration. You only need to register one callback URL
  in Google Cloud Console regardless of how many tenants you run.
</Callout>
